{"word":"ἐκρέω","slug":"ἐκρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκρέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ρεύσομαι</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἐξερρύηκα</el>) (aor2 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>ἐξερρύην</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> sense:— <i>to flow out</i> or <i>forth</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of feathers, <i>to fall off</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to fall away, disappear</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>effluere</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn. <i>to shed, let fall</i>, <el>χάριν</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}